00:06:25.070 --> 00:06:28.030
(Video playback) “Remembering that I’ll
be dead soon is the most important tool I’ve

00:06:28.030 --> 00:06:31.940
ever encountered to help me make the big choices
in life.

00:06:31.940 --> 00:06:37.860
Because almost everything, almost all external
expectations, all pride, all fear of embarrassment

00:06:37.860 --> 00:06:43.410
or failure, these things just fall away in
the face of death, leaving only what is truly

00:06:43.410 --> 00:06:44.580
important.

00:06:44.580 --> 00:06:49.970
Remembering that you are going to die is the
best way I know to avoid the trap of thinking

00:06:49.970 --> 00:07:07.650
you have something to lose.”

